<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-12-20T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-12-20T19:00:00-05:00" n="143" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/231a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WWB1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-20T19:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 20, 1916, 7 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>197. Following message to you from Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_WJE1">Willard</persName>:</p>
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>In relation to the communication which the President has sent to the
                                belligerent nations, and of which a copy has been sent you for
                                delivery to the Spanish <pb facs="0389" n="103" xml:id="pg_103"/>
                                Government, I am directly authorized by the President to cable that
                                you may say to His Majesty’s Government that, having the same end in
                                view, the time seems opportune for that Government to act, and, if
                                willing, to support the position taken by this Government.</p>
                        </quote>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>